  abstract  = "Smell perception plays a role in eating behavior and might be
               involved in the development of obesity. In fact, olfactory
               function is impaired in obesity and might depend on metabolic
               health factors. To date, the underlying neural mechanisms remain
               unclear. Here, we investigate neural processing of food-related
               odors in normal-weight, overweight and obese individuals.
